<item>
            <title>[LU-14328] Interop: sanity test 27K fails with &apos;/mnt/lustre/d27K.sanity/d27K.sanity: invalid LMV EA flags&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14328</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity test 27K fails for Lustre client version &amp;gt;= 2.13.53.54 and Lustre servers &amp;lt; 2.13.53.54. We do not see this failure with interop testing between Lustre master clients and 2.12.5/2.12.6 Lustre servers. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the suite_log for the failure at  &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/37cdc615-ade0-4d82-b271-183094775349&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/37cdc615-ade0-4d82-b271-183094775349&lt;/a&gt;, we see&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 27K: basic ops on dir with foreign LMV ================================================ 01:15:54 (1608772554)
lmv_foreign_magic: 0xcd50cd0
lmv_xattr_size: 89
lmv_foreign_type: 1
 sanity test_27K: @@@@@@ FAIL: /mnt/lustre/d27K.sanity/d27K.sanity: invalid LMV EA flags 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6273:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:2831:test_27K()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
